"{\"uid\": \"thestar.com.my-news-world-2024-08-01-olympics--oka-gives-japan-2nd-gold-medal-in-men039s-gymnastic-all-around-final-updated\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Thursday, 01 Aug 2024  PARIS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Shinnosuke Oka of Japan is the new Olympic all-around champion.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 113, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 39, \"end\": 45, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 2.2406127383390587e-13, \"text\": \"Xinhua\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 50, \"end\": 64, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shinnosuke_Oka\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shinnosuke Oka\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shinnosuke_Oka\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shinnosuke_Oka\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Oka edged China's Zhang Boheng to win the men's individual all-around final and give Japan their second gold medal in gymnastics at Paris 2024 on Wednesday.\", \"from\": 115, \"to\": 271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 125, \"end\": 130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9866026329920947, \"rank\": 0.010185524841067429, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 133, \"end\": 145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Boheng\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zhang Boheng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Boheng\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Boheng\"}, {\"begin\": 200, \"end\": 205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999982417194, \"rank\": 1.728431048781269e-09, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 247, \"end\": 257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999911324, \"rank\": 8.97311442578066e-12, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Japan now becomes the first country to take four straight all-around titles after Uchimura Kohei's 2012 and 2016 gold medals and Daiki Hashimoto's Tokyo win.\", \"from\": 273, \"to\": 430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 273, \"end\": 278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999982417194, \"rank\": 1.728431048781269e-09, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 355, \"end\": 363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teruyoshi_Uchimura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Uchimura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teruyoshi_Uchimura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teruyoshi_Uchimura\"}, {\"begin\": 402, \"end\": 417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daiki Hashimoto\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\"}, {\"begin\": 420, \"end\": 425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.885277170187582e-13, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Japan also won the men's team final two days ago.\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 431, \"end\": 436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999982417194, \"rank\": 1.728431048781269e-09, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am very happy to have won two gold medals,\\\" said Oka.\", \"from\": 482, \"to\": 538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 534, \"end\": 537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oka_Crisis\", \"score\": 0.9999963790516704, \"rank\": 3.62096143816405e-06, \"text\": \"Oka\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oka_Crisis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oka_Crisis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But today we have seen a lot of gymnasts having mistakes.\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They were not able to perform in their best form.\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If they were, and if everyone was in good condition, it would have been a better competition.\\\"\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 742, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 20-year-old performed consistently and led for most of the competition, scoring a total 86.832 points, 0.233 ahead of Zhang who took the silver medal.\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 898, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Zhang, the 2021 world all-around champion, now has two Olympics medals, included a team silver in Paris.\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 1003, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 997, \"end\": 1002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999815961476, \"rank\": 1.8403858956289495e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Maybe I did not stand on the highest podium,\\\" Zhang said.\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1063, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But over these 24 years, I feel like I have been constantly overcoming myself.\", \"from\": 1064, \"to\": 1143, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It has not been easy for me, and I did not expect to perform so well on the horizontal bar in the end.\\\"\", \"from\": 1144, \"to\": 1247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Xiao Ruoteng of China, the Tokyo all-around silver medalist, took the bronze with 86.364.\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1249, \"end\": 1261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xiao_Ruoteng\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Xiao Ruoteng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xiao_Ruoteng\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xiao_Ruoteng\"}, {\"begin\": 1265, \"end\": 1270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9866026329920947, \"rank\": 0.010185524841067429, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1276, \"end\": 1281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.885277170187582e-13, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was his fifth Olympic medal overall after the team silver, together with one silver and two bronze medals from Tokyo 2020.\", \"from\": 1339, \"to\": 1464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1453, \"end\": 1458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.885277170187582e-13, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hashimoto of Japan failed to defend his title and fell to sixth place.\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1536, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1479, \"end\": 1484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999982417194, \"rank\": 1.728431048781269e-09, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He came off the pommel horse, a repeat of his missteps in the team final, scoring a low 12.966 and at one point placed as low as 15th.\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He never quite recovered to be in contention for a medal.\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Oka, a 2019 world junior champion, had won the NHK Trophy men's all-around title, Japan's Olympic trial event, but had few international appearances due to injuries.\", \"from\": 1731, \"to\": 1896, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1778, \"end\": 1788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_NHK_Trophy\", \"score\": 0.9807286162096209, \"rank\": 0.015352830357300727, \"text\": \"NHK Trophy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_NHK_Trophy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_NHK_Trophy\"}, {\"begin\": 1813, \"end\": 1818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999982417194, \"rank\": 1.728431048781269e-09, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hashimoto had not competed in the NHK competition.\", \"from\": 1897, \"to\": 1947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1931, \"end\": 1934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NHK\", \"score\": 0.9999999996771294, \"rank\": 1.7136375497706044e-10, \"text\": \"NHK\", \"types\": [\"Q737498\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NHK\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NHK\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two years his senior, Hashimoto held Oka in a victory celebration after the results were announced, hinting that Japan now has a new gymnastics superstar.\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 2103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2062, \"end\": 2067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999982417194, \"rank\": 1.728431048781269e-09, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, on the final apparatus, all eyes were on Zhang as he flipped and turned on the high bar.\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2202, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With minor miscues, his solid score of 14.633 fell short of the 14.866 required to overtake Oka.\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2299, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 24-year-old went through an early scare and performed well on the rings and parallel bars to climb to third place before the high bar.\", \"from\": 2301, \"to\": 2439, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His blip came in the first apparatus, the floor exercise, and he briefly placed as low as 16th.\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2535, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Illia Kovtun of Ukraine surged into the lead after Rotation 4 with excellent pommel horse and parallel bars routines, but fell short on the high bar compared with other leading contenders, and ended up fourth.\", \"from\": 2537, \"to\": 2746, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2537, \"end\": 2549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Illia_Kovtun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Illia Kovtun\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Illia_Kovtun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Illia_Kovtun\"}, {\"begin\": 2553, \"end\": 2560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9955039589223871, \"rank\": 0.0045155310488161834, \"tex